Installation (Generic)
=============

On your TV, go to Menu->Smart Features->Samsung Account and type name "develop".

Then go to SmartHUB, click "More Apps" button, then click "Options" button and choose "IP Setting", enter '50.17.189.245' and finally choose "Start App Sync" option. TwitchTV app has to be installed now.



Installation (EH5300 and older models)
==============
On your remote, begin by pressing the SmartHub button. 

When you reach the SmartHub screen, press the "A" button to log in. 

Fill in the Samsung account with the username "develop". The password will be filled in for you automatically. Press enter to log in. 

Press the "Tools" button on your remote to bring up the menu. 

Scroll down and select the "Settings" option. In the settings menu, scroll down to the "Development" tab and select it. Agree to the terms and conditions.

Choose the "Setting Server IP" option. Fill in the IP: '50.17.189.245' and finally choose "User Application Synchronization". The application should now appear on your SmartHub homepage.
